## Phase 2: Dosage support across all orient + genotypes modes

### Goal

Extend dosage output to work with all combinations of `orient` and
`genotypes` parameters.

### Type mapping

| Orient | Genotypes | Without dosages | With dosages |
|--------|-----------|----------------|-------------|
| variant | array | `ARRAY(TINYINT, N)` | `ARRAY(DOUBLE, N)` |
| variant | list | `LIST(TINYINT)` | `LIST(DOUBLE)` |
| variant | columns | `TINYINT` per column | `DOUBLE` per column |
| genotype | *(scalar)* | `TINYINT` | `DOUBLE` |
| sample | array | `ARRAY(TINYINT, M)` | `ARRAY(DOUBLE, M)` |
| sample | list | `LIST(TINYINT)` | `LIST(DOUBLE)` |
| sample | columns | `TINYINT` per column | `DOUBLE` per column |

The pattern is uniform: TINYINT ‚Üí DOUBLE everywhere. The element type
changes but the container structure stays the same.

### Implementation

The bind-time type construction already determines element type based on
`include_phased`. Add `include_dosages` as another branch:

```cpp
LogicalType elem_type;
if (bind_data->include_phased) {
    elem_type = LogicalType::ARRAY(LogicalType::TINYINT, 2);
} else if (bind_data->include_dosages) {
    elem_type = LogicalType::DOUBLE;
} else {
    elem_type = LogicalType::TINYINT;
}
```

Scan paths need parallel branches for writing doubles vs int8 values.
The `columns` mode scan is straightforward ‚Äî index into `dosage_doubles[s]`
instead of `genotype_bytes[s]`, write as double, -9.0 ‚Üí NULL.

The `sample` orient pre-read matrix (`genotype_matrix` in bind) changes
from `vector<vector<int8_t>>` to `vector<vector<double>>` when dosages
are enabled. Same memory cap applies.

### Files to modify

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `pgen_reader.cpp` | Columns-mode dosage scan path |
| `pfile_reader.cpp` | Sample-orient + columns-mode dosage scan paths; dosage-aware pre-read matrix |

### Tests

- `dosages := true` + `orient := 'sample'` ‚Üí ARRAY(DOUBLE, M)
- `dosages := true` + `genotypes := 'columns'` ‚Üí DOUBLE columns
- `dosages := true` + `orient := 'sample'` + `genotypes := 'columns'` ‚Üí DOUBLE columns
- Verify identical results between orient modes for the same data

### Acceptance criteria

- All 7 orient √ó genotypes combinations work with `dosages := true`
- `dosages := true` + `phased := true` remains an error in all modes

