## Phase 3: Dosage-aware plink_freq

### Goal

Implement `plink_freq('file.pgen', dosage := true)` to compute allele
frequencies using dosage data instead of hardcall counts.

### Approach

Use `PgrGetDCounts` instead of `PgrGetCounts`. This returns dosage-weighted
allele counts when dosage data is present, falling back to hardcall counts
otherwise.

The `all_dosages` output from `PgrGetDCounts` is a uint64 sum of dosage
values (scaled by 16384), which can be converted to frequency:

```
ALT_FREQ = all_dosages[1] / (double)(total_dosage_sum)
```

Also returns `imp_r2_ptr` (imputation R¬≤ / Minimac3 INFO score) which is a
useful QC metric for imputed data ‚Äî consider adding as an output column.

### Output changes

| Column | Current | With dosage |
|--------|---------|------------|
| ALT_FREQ | From hardcall counts | From dosage sums |
| OBS_CT | Hardcall non-missing count | Same (dosage doesn't change sample count) |
| (new) IMP_R2 | ‚Äî | Imputation R¬≤ (optional, only with dosage := true) |

### Files to modify

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `plink_freq.cpp` | Replace PgrGetCounts with PgrGetDCounts when dosage=true; add IMP_R2 column |

### Tests

- Validate against `plink2 --freq` on dosage test data
- Hardcall data with dosage=true ‚Üí same frequencies as without
- IMP_R2 column present only when dosage=true

### Acceptance criteria

- `plink_freq('file.pgen', dosage := true)` returns dosage-weighted frequencies
- Results match plink2 --freq output for the same data
- IMP_R2 column included when dosage=true

